{{Infobox college wrestling team |name = The Citdadel Bulldogs |logo = Citadel Athletics Script.jpg |logo_size = 150 |university = The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina |conference = Southern Conference |conference_short = Southern Conference |division = |city = Charleston |stateabb = SC |state = South Carolina |athletic director = Larry Leckonby |coach = Rob Hjerling |tenure = 12 |arena = McAlister Field House |capacity = 6000 |nickname = Bulldogs, Cadets |current season = 2011-2012 |record = |conference finish = |ncaa finish = |update date = |color1 = Citadel Blue |color2 = White |hex1 = 9cdbff |hex2 = FFFFFF|NCAAchampion = |conference_tournament = 1967, 2004 }} '''[[The Citadel Bulldogs wrestling]]''' team represents [[The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina|The Citadel]] of [[Charleston, South Carolina|Charleston]], [[South Carolina]]. The squad is coached by Rob Hjerling. The Bulldogs are members of the [[Southern Conference]] and have been conference champions in 1967 and 2004. Dan Thompson is the only Citadel wrester to reach [[All-America]]s status at the [[NCAA Wrestling Team Championship]]. Coach Hjerling is a 1994 graduate of [[American University]]. He was named the Southern Conference's most outstanding [[collegiate wrestling]] coach in 2004. Prior to coming to The Citadel he was an assistant coach for the [[George Mason Patriots]] and [[American Eagles]]. He began his coaching career as an assitant at [[Manheim Township High School]] in [[Lancaster County, Pennsylvania|Lancaster County]], [[Pennsylvania]]. Hjerling is assisted by Jeff Ragan, Evan Sola, and Keegan Mueller.<ref> {{cite web | url = http://citadelsports.com | title = Citadel wreslting media guide | publisher = The Citadel | accessdate = August 14, 2011}}</ref>
